data.text:
The Queen and the Duke of Edinburgh were represented by Lord Taylor of Holbeach, the Prince of Wales by the Earl of Rosslyn, the Duke of York by Sir Andrew Cahn, the Princess Royal by Lord Coe, and Princess Alexandra, the Hon Lady Ogilvy, by Mrs Peter Afia at a service of thanksgiving for the life and work of Baroness (Tessa) Jowell, DBE (obituary, May 14, 2018), held on Thursday, October 16, 2018, at Southwark Cathedral.

Canon Michael Rawson, sub-dean of Southwark Cathedral, officiated, gave the bidding and pronounced the blessing.
